name: Filipino-American History Month 8.18.5 Sakada Day
text: Filipino-American History Month.  The month of October shall be known and designated as "Filipino-American History Month".  The month of October shall commemorate the contributions of Filipino-Americans to the history and heritage of Hawaii and the United States.  This month is not and shall not be construed as a state holiday. [L 2008, c 15, §2]
